Do the 28.8kbps modems support V.FC or V.FAST?

All of PPI's 28.8 modems currently support the Rockwell V.FC protocol.
When the ITU-T V.34 standard - also known as V.FAST - is finalized, an
$89 upgrade to add V.34 compatibility will be available for all PC288,
PM288, and MC288 modems.

How good is PPI's warranty and support?

Nobody else comes close.  All of PPI's modems are warrantied for life.
When ROM upgrades are made to mend operational glitches, the new chips
are available free, and when something breaks, repairs are free except
for the cost of shipping.  Technical support is available seven days a
week: 6 AM to 11 PM PST weekdays and 8 AM to 5 PM weekends.  A 24-hour
electronic BBS, the toll-free PractiFAX fax-back system, and forums on
CompuServe and America Online provide other options for information or
support.  The PPIForum staff also frequent comp.dcom.modems on Usenet,
where they field questions from users worldwide, just to be nice.

Does PPI offer rack-mount modems or network fax servers?

At the 1993 Fall Comdex show, PPI announced plans to enter the network
and rack-mount arena, showing a line of anticipated products including
racks, modems, and LAN fax servers.  These products are expected to be
officially introduced in late 1994.  Further specification and pricing
information will be available from PPI in the coming months.

Does PPI offer modems for users outside North America?

At Fall Comdex, PPI also announced plans for a family of international
modems, designed for compatibility with telephone systems and electric
wiring in Europe and Asia.  Specification and pricing information will
be available from PPI in the coming months.

What other products does PPI offer?

PPI offers two products for use with printers.  FaxMe, a cartridge for
HP LaserJet II and LaserJet III printers, enables printers to directly
receive faxes.  The Microbuffer Universal 16 is a printer buffer which
comes with 32kb of RAM installed and can be upgraded to 16mb of RAM.

