What fax capabilities do PPI modems offer? 

PPI's high-speed modems provide Group 3, Class 1 and 2 fax capability.
They support the ITU-T V.17, V.29, and V.27ter fax protocols, handling
speeds up to 14.4kbps.

My PPI modem's CD light is blinking.  Why?

The Carrier Detect light flashes to indicate changes in signal quality 
on your connection, usually caused by noise.  If the light is flashing
in a regular tempo on a 14.4 or 28.8kbps modem, it usually indicates a
retrain, in which both modems agree to raise or lower the speed of the
connection, as a way of dealing with changes in signal quality.  If it
is blinking irregularly, it may indicate the modems are having trouble
maintaining the connection due to extremely low signal quality.

How can I display the online help screens on my PPI ProClass modem?

To view your ProClass modem's online help, send the AT$H command.  You
can also send the ATI6 command to show information about your current,
or most recent, connection.

Why is my PPI modem so reluctant to hang up?

PPI modems can be set to wait a specific as long as 25 seconds after a
carrier is lost, to see whether it comes back.  If you frequently have
low signal quality, this can be quite convenient.  Sometimes though, a
PPI modem will be overly reluctant to hang up, and one user's 14.4kbps
unit refused to hang up even when someone came in on call-waiting.  In
cases like this, it's probably a good idea to set the value of the S10
register to a low number - 10 or less - and if that doesn't work, call
technical support to see whether there's a known glitch.

