I bought a PPI modem for my BBS.  Where can I get a setup file?

The PPI support BBS usually has some setup files available for several
types of BBSes.  If your system runs WWIV, you can look on the WWIVnet
PPI discussion forum for setup files and other information, or ask The
Sandman (1@3462) or Aldur (1@3314) where to look.  The Sand Castle BBS
hosts the PPI SIG, if you wish to subscribe.

How can I add my old PM14400FXSA modem to my Mac's Modem Tool?

Jim Hebert's AMT-MoreModems file (AMT-MoreModem.sit.hqx on the nearest
Macintosh FTP site) adds you to add a variety of modems to Modem Tool.
The PM14400FXSA is among these, and an icon of it is also included.


